# Framework7 React + Konsta UI + React Router Rules

## Core Frameworks
- **Framework7 React**: Primary framework for mobile app structure
- **Konsta UI React**: UI component library built with Tailwind CSS
- **React Router**: Navigation and routing (integrate with Framework7 router when needed)

## Component Structure

### Framework7 App Structure
- Always use `App` component as the root wrapper with `theme` prop (`ios` or `md`)
- Use `View` component for main app views with `main` prop
- Use `Page` component for individual pages
- Use `Navbar` component for page headers with `title` prop
- Use `Toolbar` component for bottom toolbars
- Use `Link` component for navigation instead of regular anchor tags

### Page Structure Pattern
```typescript
import { Page, Navbar, Block } from 'framework7-react';
import { Appbar, BlockTitle } from 'konsta/react';

const MyPage: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <Page>
      <Navbar title="Page Title" />
      <Block>
        {/* Page content */}
      </Block>
    </Page>
  );
};
```

## Konsta UI Components

### Use Konsta Components for UI Elements
- Use `Appbar` for app bars/navigation bars
- Use `Block`, `BlockTitle`, `BlockHeader`, `BlockFooter` for content sections
- Use `Button` for buttons (with `colors` prop for theming)
- Use `Card` for card components
- Use `List`, `ListItem`, `ListInput` for lists and forms
- Use `Preloader` for loading indicators
- Use `Icon` for icons
- Use `Badge` for badges/notifications
- Use `Chip` for chips/tags
- Use `Link` for links
- Use `Navbar` for navigation bars
- Use `Panel` for side panels
- Use `Popover` for popovers
- Use `Sheet` for bottom sheets
- Use `Toast` for toast notifications
- Use `Dialog` for dialogs/modals
- Use `ActionSheet` for action sheets
- Use `Segmented` for segmented controls
- Use `Toggle` for toggle switches
- Use `Checkbox` for checkboxes
- Use `Radio` for radio buttons
- Use `Range` for sliders
- Use `Progressbar` for progress bars
- Use `Searchbar` for search inputs
- Use `Swiper` for carousels/swipers
- Use `Tabs` for tab navigation
- Use `Tabbar` for tab bars
- Use `Toolbar` for toolbars

### Konsta Component Props
- Always use `colors` prop for theming (e.g., `colors={{ material: 'blue', ios: 'blue' }}`)
- Use `ios` and `material` props for platform-specific styling
- Use `rounded` prop for rounded corners
- Use `bordered` prop for borders
- Use `raised` prop for elevation/shadow

## Styling

### Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for styling (Konsta UI is built on Tailwind)
- Use `dark:` prefix for dark mode styles
- Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, etc.) when needed
- Prefer Tailwind classes over inline styles

### Framework7 CSS Variables
- Use Framework7 CSS variables for theming when appropriate
- Use `--f7-theme-color` for primary theme color
- Use `--f7-navbar-bg-color` for navbar background
- Use `--f7-toolbar-bg-color` for toolbar background

## Routing

### Framework7 Router
- Use Framework7's built-in router for navigation within Framework7 views
- Use `Link` component with `href` prop for navigation
- Use `f7router` prop to access router instance when needed
- Use `f7route` prop to access route data

### React Router Integration
- When using React Router, integrate it with Framework7's router
- Use React Router for top-level routing if needed
- Ensure Framework7 router works within React Router routes

## React Patterns

### Component Definition
- Always use functional components with React.FC
- Use arrow function syntax: `const MyComponent: React.FC<Props> = (props) => { return <></>; }`
- Use `type` instead of `interface` for prop types
- Never use `any` type unless absolutely necessary

### Component Organization
- Put public functions at the top, private at the bottom
- Keep components concise - fewer lines is better
- Avoid single-line/unwrapped if blocks

### Export Patterns
- **Routes only**: Use default exports for route files (`app/routes/**/*.tsx`)
- **Everything else**: Always use named exports (components, utilities, services, controllers, etc.)
- Examples:
  - Route: `export default LoginPage;` âś…
  - Component: `export { LoginForm };` âś… (NOT `export default LoginForm;` âťŚ)
  - Utility: `export { checkAuthClient };` âś…
  - Service: `export { authService };` âś…

### Hooks
- Use Framework7 hooks: `useFramework7`, `useTheme`, `useToolbar`, `useNavbar`
- Use React hooks appropriately (useState, useEffect, etc.)
- Use Konsta UI hooks when available

## State Management

### Framework7 Store
- Use Framework7's store for global state when appropriate
- Use `f7store` to access store instance
- Use `f7ready` to ensure Framework7 is initialized

### React State
- Use React hooks for component-local state
- Use Context API or state management library for shared state

## Platform Detection

### Theme Detection
- Use `useTheme` hook to detect current theme (`ios` or `md`)
- Apply platform-specific styles using theme detection
- Use `ios` and `material` props on Konsta components

### Device Detection
- Use Framework7's device detection utilities when needed
- Apply device-specific optimizations

## Best Practices

### Performance
- Use `React.memo` for expensive components when appropriate
- Lazy load routes/pages when possible
- Optimize images and assets

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation works

### Code Quality
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Use TypeScript strictly (no `any` unless necessary)
- Follow consistent naming conventions

## Import Patterns

### TypeScript Path Alias
- **`@`** points to the project root directory
- Use `@/` prefix for all imports from project root to avoid deep relative paths
- Examples:
  - `@/libs/auth/auth.controller` instead of `../../../../libs/auth/auth.controller`
  - `@/app/components/layout/AuthLayout` instead of `../../components/layout/AuthLayout`
  - `@/app/utils/auth` instead of `../../utils/auth`
- Always prefer `@/` imports over relative paths (`../`, `../../`, etc.) for better maintainability

### Framework7 Imports
```typescript
import { App, View, Page, Navbar, Toolbar, Link } from 'framework7-react';
```

### Konsta UI Imports
```typescript
import { Appbar, Block, BlockTitle, Button, Card } from 'konsta/react';
```

### React Router Imports
```typescript
import { BrowserRouter, Routes, Route, Link as RouterLink } from 'react-router-dom';
```

## Example Component Structure

```typescript
import { Page, Navbar } from 'framework7-react';
import { Block, BlockTitle, Button } from 'konsta/react';
import { useFramework7 } from 'framework7-react';

type MyPageProps = {
  title?: string;
};

const MyPage: React.FC<MyPageProps> = ({ title = 'Default Title' }) => {
  const f7 = useFramework7();
  
  const handleClick = () => {
    f7.dialog.alert('Button clicked!');
  };
  
  return (
    <Page>
      <Navbar title={title} />
      <Block>
        <BlockTitle>Content</BlockTitle>
        <Button onClick={handleClick}>Click Me</Button>
      </Block>
    </Page>
  );
};

export default MyPage;
```

## Notes
- Framework7 provides its own router - use it for navigation within Framework7 views
- Konsta UI components are built on Tailwind CSS - use Tailwind utilities for styling
- Always test on both iOS and Material Design themes
- Ensure components work well on mobile devices
- Use Framework7's built-in components and utilities when available

